cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about video object segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a novel GAN architecture for learning spatio-temporal object models over finite temporal windows. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
